entry.title: Hydrologic Outlook issued August 11 at 11:29AM CDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...ADDITIONAL HEAVY RAIN TUESDAY WILL LIKELY CAUSE MORE FLOODING... THE SET UP WILL BEGIN WITH A COLD FRONT OVER NORTHWEST SECTIONS OF THE STATE TUESDAY MORNING. WITH PLENTY OF MOISTURE IN PLACE...NUMEROUS SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS ARE EXPECTED TO DEVELOP

entry.title: Dense Fog Advisory issued August 12 at 12:25AM EDT until August 12 at 10:00AM EDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...AREAS OF DENSE FOG EXPECTED OVERNIGHT... .THE SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS OF THE PAST SEVERAL DAYS HAVE LEFT THE GROUND ACROSS MOST OF EAST KENTUCKY QUITE MOIST. THIS WILL COMBINE WITH PARTIALLY CLEAR SKIES AND LIGHT WINDS TO GENERATE WIDESPREAD FOG. THIS FOG WILL BE THICKEST IN THE VALLEYS AND DEVELOP THERE EARLIER IN THE NIGHT. THE FOG SHOULD LIFT AND BREAK UP BY 10 AM
